questions.explanation:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The correct answer is - &lt;u&gt;A-II, B-IV, C-III, D-I&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle; font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/span&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Case Study (A-II)&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Case studies focus on in-depth analysis of a specific case, group, or individual.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;They often face the difficulty of &lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;limited generalizability&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; due to the unique nature of the subject under study.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Correlational Research (B-IV)&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;This research method examines the &lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;relationship&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; or association between two variables.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It does not establish a &lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;cause-and-effect relationship&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;; it only highlights the nature of the relationship.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Observation (C-III)&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;In this method, researchers observe participants&amp;#39; behavior or phenomena in natural settings.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The behavior of individuals may &lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;change&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; if they become aware that they are being observed, known as the &amp;quot;Hawthorne Effect.&amp;quot;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Survey Research (D-I)&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Surveys collect self-reported data from respondents using questionnaires or interviews.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;A major difficulty is that participants may &lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;distort&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; responses to appear socially acceptable, leading to biased results.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle; font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/span&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Case Study&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It is widely used in fields like psychology, sociology, and education.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It provides &lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;detailed insights&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; into specific cases but lacks external validity.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Correlational Research&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Correlations can be &lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;positive, negative, or zero&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Statistical techniques like the Pearson correlation coefficient measure the strength of the relationship.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Observation&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Can be of two types: &lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;participant observation&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; (researcher is involved) and &lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;non-participant observation&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Ensuring ethical guidelines, such as informed consent, is crucial in observational studies.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Survey Research&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Surveys can be conducted using &lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;online, paper, or face-to-face methods&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Effective surveys require well-designed questions to minimize bias and enhance reliability.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The correct answer is - &lt;u&gt;Constructionism&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle; font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/span&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Constructionism&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It is an &lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;ontological orientation&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; that posits that &lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;reality&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; is not objective but is &lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;socially constructed&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; through human interactions and interpretations.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;In qualitative research, constructionism emphasizes understanding how individuals or groups &lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;construct meaning&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; within their social and cultural contexts.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Researchers adopting this perspective aim to explore the &lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;subjective experiences&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; and the &lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;constructed realities&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; of participants rather than focusing on objective, measurable facts.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It contrasts with &lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;objectivism&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;, which assumes that reality exists independently of human perception.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle; font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/span&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Other Ontological Orientations:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Objectivism:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;

		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;Assumes that &lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;social phenomena&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; and their meanings exist &lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;independently&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; of social actors.&lt;/li&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;Often associated with &lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;quantitative research&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; and a positivist approach.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Positivism:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;
		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;A philosophical stance emphasizing the use of &lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;scientific methods&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; to study observable phenomena.&lt;/li&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;Typically linked to &lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;quantitative research&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;, focusing on objectivity and generalizability.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Deductive Approach:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;
		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;Involves testing &lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;pre-existing theories&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; or hypotheses through empirical observation.&lt;/li&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;Not directly relevant to the ontological orientation of qualitative research, which typically employs an &lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;inductive&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; approach.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Qualitative Research and Constructionism:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Qualitative research methods such as &lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;interviews&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; and &lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;ethnography&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; are often aligned with constructionism.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;These methods aim to explore participants&amp;#39; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;subjective interpretations&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; and the processes through which they create meaning.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
